laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild fatty infiltration of the transplant liver, esophageal/paraesophageal varices, intra-abdominal collateral vessels, stable right-sided adrenal nodules, and mild thickening of the left adrenal gland.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: No findings of anastomotic stenosis; previous findings of focal high-grade stenosis involving the proximal celiac artery with mild post-stenotic dilatation were consistent.
